@page "/"

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Snake Client Project - Home</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f0f23 0%, #1a1a3e 100%);
            font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
            position: relative;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            color: #00ff00;
            min-height: 100vh;
        }

        /* Animated background grid */
        body::before {
            content: '';
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            background-image: 
                linear-gradient(rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.05) 1px, transparent 1px),
                linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.05) 1px, transparent 1px);
            background-size: 30px 30px;
            pointer-events: none;
            z-index: 0;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 2rem;
            position: relative;
            z-index: 1;
        }

        .header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
            padding: 2rem;
            border: 2px solid #00ff00;
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
            box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.3);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 3rem;
            color: #00ff00;
            text-shadow: 
                0 0 10px #00ff00,
                0 0 20px #00ff00,
                0 0 30px #00ff00;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        }

        .authors {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: #00ccff;
            text-shadow: 0 0 5px #00ccff;
            letter-spacing: 0.05em;
        }

        .section {
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
            border: 1px solid #00ff00;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.2);
        }

        h2 {
            color: #00ff00;
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            text-shadow: 0 0 10px #00ff00;
            border-bottom: 2px solid #00ff00;
            padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        h3 {
            color: #00ccff;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            margin-top: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
            text-shadow: 0 0 5px #00ccff;
        }

        p {
            line-height: 1.8;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            color: #88ff88;
        }

        ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding-left: 0;
        }

        li {
            padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem;
            position: relative;
            color: #88ff88;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        li::before {
            content: '▸';
            position: absolute;
            left: 0;
            color: #00ff00;
            text-shadow: 0 0 5px #00ff00;
        }

        .highlight {
            background: rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.1);
            padding: 1rem;
            border-left: 3px solid #00ff00;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }

        .status-works {
            color: #00ff00;
            text-shadow: 0 0 5px #00ff00;
        }

        .status-issues {
            color: #ffaa00;
            text-shadow: 0 0 5px #ffaa00;
        }

        strong {
            color: #00ff00;
            text-shadow: 0 0 3px #00ff00;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>SNAKE CLIENT PROJECT</h1>
            <p class="authors">by Brady Nelson & Charlie Adair</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Project Overview</h2>
            <p>
                This project implements a networked multiplayer Snake game client using Blazor WebAssembly. 
                The client communicates with a game server to enable real-time multiplayer gameplay with 
                custom graphics.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Design Decisions</h2>

            <h3>User Interface</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Theme:</strong> Retro arcade aesthetic with neon green/purple color scheme.</li>
                <li><strong>Controls:</strong> Use WASD or the arrow keys to move the snake.</li>
                <li><strong>HUD:</strong> Your score is shown above your snake; the scores of the top 8 players, as well as FPS, are shown in the top left of the screen.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Client Logic</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>JSON Deserialization:</strong> The client receives data packets from the server as JSON files, deserializes them into game objects.</li>
                <li><strong>Canvas Drawing:</strong> The BECanvas element in Blazor handles the drawing of the objects according to the assignment specs.</li>
                <li><strong>Networking:</strong> The client uses a wrapper class of TcpClient to communicate with the server.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Special Features</h2>
            
            <div class="highlight">
                <p><strong>Feature 1: [Feature Name]</strong></p>
                <p>Description...</p>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight">
                <p><strong>Feature 2: [Feature Name]</strong></p>
                <p>Description...</p>
            </div>

            <div class="highlight">
                <p><strong>Feature 3: [Feature Name]</strong></p>
                <p>Description...</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Known Issues</h2>
            <ul class="status-issues">
                <li>[Any bugs or limitations]</li>
                <li>[Performance considerations]</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>Additional Notes</h2>
            <p>
                ...
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>